
Overview of noun conviction

The noun conviction has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                     
1. (19) conviction, strong belief, article of faith -- (an unshakable belief in something without need for proof or evidence)
2. (3) conviction, judgment of conviction, condemnation, sentence -- ((criminal law) a final judgment of guilty in a criminal case and the punishment that is imposed; "the conviction came as no surprise")
